WRITING.TITLE: Praecantatio Source Issues
WRITING.TEXT: For my alchemy, I'm trying to create a Praecantatio Vis Crystal and I heard that Salis Mundus was a good source for praecantatio. Though, when I input the Salis Mundus into the crucible and click it with a quartz silver, I get a Potentia Vis Crystal instead, since it also has five potentia. Is there a way to get the praecantatio instead of the potentia or is there another source I could use instead? P.S. I have this problem with a lot of crystals too, actually. I use an item that has two or more different aspects and I end up getting a primary aspect instead of the compound aspect I want. It's annoying.

WRITING.TITLE: Problems with converting UTAU files and importing into Audacity...
WRITING.TEXT: I'm not sure if anyone else has ever experienced this, but I just finished the vocals for my newest UTAU cover and I usually convert it to a .wav, .mp4, or .ogg file to import it into Audacity so I can do further edits with the vocals and the instrumental. I usually have no problem converting them and all was well until I imported the new .wav file into Audacity. I played it, and it seemed to convert Teto's voice into a piano. I thought that was weird, so I converted it into a .ogg file to test. The same result came out... I tried a couple more converters and the second one gave me a long series of high frequency beeps sort of in the tune of the melody. I just want to know if anyone else had this problem and if they ever had a solution to it... I doubt it, though. This has never happened on any of my other songs, they converted just fine. :/

Hey! I like the percussion in the background! I think it would be a lot more interesting if you added a counter melody and switched things up a bit now and then, the first 30 seconds were nice, but music needs variety! It's a nice tune and would sound a lot better with some other melodies with it. Good luck! Edit: Also, in a way, I think the simple repeating melody does reflect the title of "Heavy," and it does fit well, this is just for future reference, lol

Wow, this is actually really, really good in my opinion. I really like the mystery/dread that is in the song. And WOW, that dubstep like beat about a quarter way through was really awesome! Anyway, I think the only real criticism I have is that the intro might have been just a little long, but it was still great! Nice job :0
Oh wow. This song is great, how are you not a famous musician at the moment? I really like the beat, it's interesting and moves a lot. The instruments are relaxing and fit well. Nice job!
That bass is really nice and fits well with the song! Maybe you could have a little more backing melodies in the background, but with this style of music, it might not be needed. Well done!

Wow! I am in LOVE with the instruments, especially the one in the beginning to play the melody! I really love the slow and relaxing beat and the transition. :O I don't even have any criticism, I'm blown away lol Nicely done, I need to listen to your other tracks ASAP

I think they sounded alright and fit in with the song, but they didn't seem to be on the same beats at different parts in the song. They sounded cool, but they didn't seem to have a set tempo and it sort of made them seem all over the place. You have potential, keep it up! Can't wait to hear more.
Wow, this is really good! The only thing I would really even suggest is adding a few backing melodies to keep things spiced up, especially since there's no lyrics involved. :) Keep it up!
I used to use an electric keyboard to plug up into my computer, but I can't find the plug since I've moved a few times. I just find it easier to draw in notes on the piano roll.

Well... while V4 is more stable, I think you should try to get V5. The voices and singing styles are beautiful and it's very, very easy to use. The attack and release options are useful and The emotion tool works wonders. Overall, I think V5 has better quality voices. The only voice I've really experimented with was Gumi English, so I'm not really sure about any other voicebanks. About the bugs, I've only had one major bug and it was that V5 would crash when I touched the pencil tool, and I found that uninstalling and reinstalling fixed everything, so honestly if you have problems like that, just uninstall and reinstall. TL;DR: I would say V5 because of the higher quality voices.
